<div class="wrapper wrapper_padding clearfix">
  <div class="col-1 about homepage_content">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <hr>
    <p>I'm a designer &amp; developer living in Castle Rock, Colorado.</p>
    <p>I spend my days as a senior graphic designer for Arrow Electronics and my side hustles include running a <a href="http://whiteoakhammocks.com">hammock company</a>, a <a href="http://alpineapparel.co">screen printing company</a>, and a <a href="http://ocoeecreative.com">web agency</a>.</p>
    <p>You can find me on <a href="https://twitter.com/jessepoteet" target="_blank">Twitter</a>, <a href="https://instagram.com/jpoteet" target="_blank">Instagram</a>, <a href="https://facebook.com/jpoteet6" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, and blogging here about what I'm learning in business and development. I'm also sharing some design work on <a href="https://dribbble.com/jessepoteet" target="_blank">Dribbble</a> and some dev work on <a href="https://github.com/jpoteet" target="_blank">Github</a>.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-2 homepage_content">
    <h2>Articles</h2>
    <hr>
    <% @posts.each do |post| %>
    <h3><%= link_to post.title, post %></h3>
    <p class="date"><%= post.created_at.strftime("%A, %b, %d") %></p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <div class="col-3 homepage_content">
    <h2>Projects</h2>
    <hr>
    <% @projects.each do |project| %>
    <h3><%= link_to  project.title, project %></h3>
    <p class="date"><%= project.created_at.strftime("%A, %b, %d") %></p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
